>goth
Seems she has to be European in origin, almost by definition, to have a solid goth edge. If the story stays in Europe or she travels to America is probably the decision here. Maybe she came from Germany, somewhere a bit to the East. Romania even, not too far to travel in a reasonable time for the period. A pagan spirit animal driven from her homeland to the West? From there maybe settled in Scotland or took the long boat ride across the Atlantic.

Does the story begin with her already in a relationship with a human? Or does she find that along the way? Is she an actual fox taking human form? Or more of an anthro fox that can pass as human? Or, is your world one where fox anthros are part of reality? Without magic, you lose the ability to shapeshift or obscure her true form, so foxgirls/foxfolk would have to be a known species.

If there are minor magics possible, then she may appear in human disguise to most people. Only certain people with skills & abilities (shamans, etc.) might see through her disguise. And the one(s) she trusts enough to show her true self. If in disguise, that's a major plot point as she tries to protect her true identity.

Her age and lifespan are important questions. Is she young and lost in the world? Older and worldly? Does she require some form of worship to remain alive? Maybe the love of her human is what sustains her. Do you see her as more pagan and witchy? Or more of a princess from a fallen castle, and deep family history tied to that?
